<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[189,303,616,642]" box="[189,303,616,642]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,616,642]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,616,642]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[189,1398,662,724]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
The specimens correspond well with the original description (
<bibRefCitation author="Marcus E." box="[903,1058,662,689]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="1 - 3" refId="ref17301" refString="Marcus E. 1946. Batillipes pennaki, a new marine tardigrade from the North and South American Atlantic coast. Comunicaciones Zoologicas del Museo de Historia Natural de Montevideo 2: 1 - 3." type="journal article" year="1946">Marcus 1946</bibRefCitation>
) and subsquent diagnosis (
<bibRefCitation author="de Zio S." pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="1 - 7" refId="ref16482" refString="de Zio S. 1962. Descrizione di Batillipes annulatus n. sp. e note su Batillipes pennaki Marcus, nuovo rinvenimento nel Mediterraneo (Hetrotardigrada). Annuario dell Istituto e Museo di Zoologia della Universita di Napoli 14 (6): 1 - 7." type="journal article" year="1962">de Zio 1962</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Pollock L. W." box="[311,483,697,724]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="38 - 52" refId="ref17583" refString="Pollock L. W. 1970 a. Batillipes dicrocercus n. sp., Stygarctus granulatus n. sp. and other Tardigrada from Woods Hole, Massachusetts, U. S. A. Transactions of the American Microscopical Society 89 (1): 38 - 52. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 3224613" type="journal article" year="1970">Pollock 1970a</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="McKirdy D. J." box="[495,672,697,724]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="177 - 223" refId="ref17384" refString="McKirdy D. J. 1975. Batillipes (Heterotardigrada): Comparison of six species from Florida (USA) and a discussion of taxonomic characters within the genus. Memorie dell'Istituto Italiano di Idrobiologia 32 (Supplement): 177 - 223." type="journal article" year="1975">McKirdy 1975</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ramazzotti G. &amp; Maucci W." box="[684,1013,697,724]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="1 - 1012" refId="ref17771" refString="Ramazzotti G. &amp; Maucci W. 1983. Il phylum Tardigrada - III Edizione. Memorie dell'Istituto Italiano di Idrobiologia 41: 1 - 1012." type="journal article" year="1983">Ramazzotti &amp; Maucci 1983</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Zawierucha K. &amp; Grzelak K. &amp; Kotwicki L. &amp; Michalczyk L. &amp; Kaczmarek L." box="[1025,1301,697,724]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="801 - 808" refId="ref18373" refString="Zawierucha K., Grzelak K., Kotwicki L., Michalczyk L. &amp; Kaczmarek L. 2013. Batillipes pennaki Marcus, 1946, a new addition to the Thai tardigrade fauna, with an overview of literature on the species. Pakistan Journal of Zoology 45 (3): 801 - 808." type="journal article" year="2013">
Zawierucha 
<emphasis box="[1171,1229,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="16.[189,342,763,789]" box="[189,342,763,789]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,342,763,789]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,342,763,789]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Distribution</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[189,1399,809,942]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
A common, worldwide distributed intertidal species that can occur in subtidal zones (for a more detailed geographic distribution see 
<bibRefCitation author="Kaczmarek L. &amp; Bartels P. J. &amp; Roszkowska M. &amp; Nelson D. R." box="[512,781,845,872]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="1 - 189" refId="ref17167" refString="Kaczmarek L., Bartels P. J., Roszkowska M. &amp; Nelson D. R. 2015. The zoogeography of marine Tardigrada. Zootaxa 4037 (1): 1 - 189. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4037.1.1" type="journal article" year="2015">
Kaczmarek 
<emphasis box="[653,704,845,871]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">et al</emphasis>
. 2015
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marcus" authorityYear="1946" box="[800,1012,845,871]" class="Heterotardigrada" family="Batillipedidae" genus="Batillipes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Arthrotardigrada" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="species" species="pennaki">
<emphasis box="[800,1012,845,871]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Batillipes pennaki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was already known for 
<collectingCountry box="[1292,1394,845,871]" name="Portugal" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Portugal</collectingCountry>
, but up till now, only recorded in the northern region (
<bibRefCitation author="Rubal M. &amp; Veiga P. &amp; Fontoura P. &amp; Santos E. &amp; Sousa-Pinto I." box="[818,1025,880,907]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="747 - 754" refId="ref18050" refString="Rubal M., Veiga P., Fontoura P., Santos E. &amp; Sousa-Pinto I. 2016. Biodiversity of marine tardigrades from the northern coast of Portugal (Iberian Peninsula). Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 178: 747 - 754. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / zoj. 12462" type="journal article" year="2016">
Rubal 
<emphasis box="[898,950,880,906]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">et al</emphasis>
. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
) both on sandy beaches as well as on rocky shores.
</paragraph>
